column10: I liked that it presented an option based on the conditions listed. The way that we used it here I do not think would be very helpful but, if you just had to look up words and phrases and it showed you a video that could be helpful. Searching for the sign without knowing what it was seemed complicated.
column11: If more options were presented based on the criterion there may be a better opportunity to find what the meaning is. The Ad's were also frustrating, if there is anyway to remove the Ads that could create a better user experience.

column10: I liked the format and the sequence of questions. I think a program similar to this would be very helpful when learning ASL.
column11: The quality of the pictures and videos was blurry. Having the pictures and videos at a higher quality would help.
